able_d4463e1_d4464e1_d4465e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">TXT</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dxv1665702661285__table_d4463e1_d4464e1_d4465e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">No</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dxv1665702661285__table_d4463e1_d4464e1_d4465e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">No</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dxv1665702661285__table_d4463e1_d4464e1_d4465e1__entry__4\">\n<p class=\"p\">No</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dxv1665702661285__table_d4463e1_d4464e1_d4465e1__entry__5\">\n<p class=\"p\">No</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dxv1665702661285__table_d4463e1_d4464e1_d4465e1__entry__6\">\n<p class=\"p\">No</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dxv1665702661285__table_d4463e1_d4464e1_d4465e1__entry__7\">\n<p class=\"p\">No</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dxv1665702661285__table_d4463e1_d4464e1_d4465e1__entry__8\"></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dxv1665702661285__table_d4463e1_d4464e1_d4465e1__entry__9\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"9\" headers=\"dxv1665702661285__table_d4463e1_d4464e1_d4465e1__entry__1 dxv1665702661285__table_d4463e1_d4464e1_d4465e1__entry__2 dxv1665702661285__table_d4463e1_d4464e1_d4465e1__entry__3 dxv1665702661285__table_d4463e1_d4464e1_d4465e1__entry__4 dxv1665702661285__table_d4463e1_d4464e1_d4465e1__entry__5 dxv1665702661285__table_d4463e1_d4464e1_d4465e1__entry__6 dxv1665702661285__table_d4463e1_d4464e1_d4465e1__entry__7 dxv1665702661285__table_d4463e1_d4464e1_d4465e1__entry__8 dxv1665702661285__table_d4463e1_d4464e1_d4465e1__entry__9\"><sup class=\"ph sup\">1</sup> By default, stepped hitlists are\n                     disabled. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lct1665702664877.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lct1665702664877.html\" title=\"The SQLite database has very limited support for concurrency. This has implications for the default locking strategy, hit list behavior, and transaction length.\">Locking Considerations for SQLite</a>.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hcs1665703005814.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>read</a><p>Fetch an occurrence from the hitlist.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ffb1665702661430.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>u_where</a><p>Provide a DBMS-independent profile for selection with read and selectdb.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ubp1665702661359.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>selectdb</a><p>Calculate aggregate values for specified fields in the database.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tut1665702663138.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Data Retrieval</a><p>Every DBMS connector recognizes the same set of connector I/O requests. When retrieving data from the database, Uniface selects the required data with the Select connector request, and fetches it into the component with the Fetch connector request. Uniface uses the Select request to create a partially built hitlist called a stepped hitlist.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gwm1665702661923.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Stepped Hitlists</a><p>Uniface uses the Select request to create a partially built hitlist called a stepped hitlist. This mechanism ensures that a limited number of occurrences are fetched from the database, even though a large number of occurrences match the retrieve profile entered by the user.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fwc1665702664241.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Data Paging in Web Applications</a><p>Data paging is a mechanism for grouping records retrieved from a database into discrete chunks (data pages), each one displaying a limited number of records. It limits the number of records fetched from the database, even when a large number of records match the query, thereby providing better performance.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7422291\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7422291\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Data Retrieval Support Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 08, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Data Retrieval Support In response to read and selectdb ProcScript instructions, Uniface issues connector requests to select data into a hitlist and fetch it into the calling component. Special considerations and restrictions may apply for some databases. Most databases support stepped hitlists to improve performance. For some databases, the use of selectdb functions may be restricted, depending on the DBMS data type of the field. The offset option of the read ProcScript statement is not supported by all connectors. Record-level databases do not support the where , order by , and u_where arguments to the read statement or the retrieveSequential trigger. For more information, see read and selectdb . For details about the data retrieval support provided by specific connectors, see the following table. Table 1. Data Retrieval Support Connector Stepped hitlist? where order by u_where offset selectdb retrieveSequential Trigger Details DB2 Yes Yes Yes Yes Yes Yes Yes For more information, see Data Retrieval on DB2 . Informix Yes Yes Yes Yes No Yes Yes For more information, see Data Retrieval on Informix . LDAP Yes Yes Yes Yes No Yes Yes For more information, see Data Storage and Retrieval on LDAP and Map LDAP Entries to Uniface Entities . MS-SQL Server Yes Yes Yes Yes Yes Yes Yes For more information, see Data Retrieval on Microsoft SQL Server . MySQL Yes Yes Yes Yes Yes Yes Yes For more information, see Data Retrieval on MySQL . ODBC Yes Yes Yes Yes No Yes Yes For more information, see Data Retrieval on ODBC . Oracle Yes Yes Yes Yes Yes Yes Yes For more information, see Data Retrieval on Oracle . PostgreSQL Yes Yes Yes Yes Yes Yes Yes SEQ No No Yes Yes No Yes No For more information, see Data Retrieval on SEQ . SQLite Yes 1 Yes Yes Yes Yes Yes Yes For more information, see Data Retrieval on SQLite and Locking Considerations for SQLite . Sybase Yes Yes Yes Yes No Yes No For more information, see Data Retrieval on Sybase . TXT No No No No No No 1 By default, stepped hitlists are disabled. For more information, see Locking Considerations for SQLite . Related Links read Fetch an occurrence from the hitlist. u_where Provide a DBMS-independent profile for selection with read and selectdb. selectdb Calculate aggregate values for specified fields in the database. Data Retrieval Every DBMS connector recognizes the same set of connector I/O requests. When retrieving data from the database, Uniface selects the required data with the Select connector request, and fetches it into the component with the Fetch connector request. Uniface uses the Select request to create a partially built hitlist called a stepped hitlist. Stepped Hitlists Uniface uses the Select request to create a partially built hitlist called a stepped hitlist. This mechanism ensures that a limited number of occurrences are fetched from the database, even though a large number of occurrences match the retrieve profile entered by the user. Data Paging in Web Applications Data paging is a mechanism for grouping records retrieved from a database into discrete chunks (data pages), each one displaying a limited number of records. It limits the number of records fetched from the database, even when a large number of records match the query, thereby providing better performance. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}